text: Calasetta (Câdesédda, Cal' e Sèda) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sud Sardegna in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 2,923 people lived there. Its area is 31.06 km². It is 9 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of South Sardinia
title: Calasetta
